{"id":"271951852_Modular_Sequent_Calculi_for_Classical_Modal_Logics","abstract":"This paper develops sequent calculi for several classical modal logics. Utilizing a polymodal translation of the standard modal language, we are able to establish a base system for the minimal classical modal logic E from which we generate extensions (to include M, C, and N) in a modular manner. Our systems admit contraction and cut admissibility, and allow a systematic proof-search procedure of formal derivations.","authors":["David R. Gilbert","Paolo Maffezioli"],"meta":["February 2014Studia Logica 103(1)","DOI:10.1007/s11225-014-9556-1"],"references":["228917781_Kripke_completeness_revisited","225788229_Proof_Analysis_in_Modal_Logic","2534370_Labelled_Tableaux_for_Non-Normal_Modal_Logics","2318216_From_Classical_to_Normal_Modal_Logics","2313711_Normal_Monomodal_Logics_Can_Simulate_All_Others","316792725_Advice_on_Modal_Logic","299164235_Labelled_tableaux_for_non-normal_modal_logics","275166248_Proof_analysis_beyond_geometric_theories_From_rule_systems_to_systems_of_rules","272040147_Proofs_and_Countermodels_in_Non-Classical_Logics","267079784_Sequent_calculi_for_monotonic_modal_logics","266832160_Admissibility_of_cut_in_congruent_modal_logics","265817915_Proof_analysis_A_contribution_to_Hilbert's_last_problem","265366904_Labelled_Deductive_Systems","262278521_Abduction_in_Labelled_Deductive_Systems","251467766_Modal_proof_theory","250792197_Tableau_Games_for_Coalition_Logic_and_Alternating-time_Temporal_Logic_theory_and_implementation","242943276_On_the_Proof_Theory_of_the_Modal_Logic_Grz","242640524_Modal_Logic_An_Introduction","238719836_The_Collected_Papers_of_Gerard_Gentzen","229446199_Universal_Grammar","220690164_Structural_Proof_Theory","220297918_Sequent_Calculi_and_Decision_Procedures_for_Weak_Modal_Systems","23951982_Neighbourhood_Structures_Bisimilarity_and_Basic_Model_Theory","2911849_Monotonic_Modal_Logics"]}